Health & wellness is the **only consumer category where more people plan to spend *more* in 2026 than less** — and nearly **30% of Gen Z and millennials** say they prioritize wellness "a lot more" than a year ago. The cultural shift is clear: the story of 2026 isn't harder workouts — it's the business of resting better. Sleep tech alone is already a multi-billion-dollar market growing double digits.

For anyone building in wellness, recovery is the broadest, most accessible topic there is. It pulls in a wide audience and opens every adjacent conversation: sleep, nutrition, wearables, and the coaching that ties them together.
